    "ICD-10-PCS section (00QM) rather than the correct Peripheral Nervous ",
    "System section (01QM), representing a systematic ICD-10-PCS coding error. ",
    "Only %d discharges were correctly coded to the PNS section. No encounters ",
    "were identified with Supplement (01UM) or Reposition (01SM) codes, ",
    "indicating that facial nerve grafting and transposition are not captured ",
    "in NIS under alternative procedure classifications. The inpatient volume ",
    "was insufficient for co-occurring procedure analysis; NASS was therefore ",
    "designated the primary database. The 00QM miscoding pattern, identified ",
    "in %.1f%% of inpatient facial nerve repair encounters, represents a ",
    "clinically significant administrative coding error that would cause these ",
